Scrum - Artifacts Workbook
Definition of Done
Definition	Done includes everything needed, including user acceptance rating, for the current increment to complete.
Purpose	This is to have a properly defined method to when the team should decide they are finished with the current story point.

Product Backlog
Definition	It is used to document the wants and needs for “stuff”, which is prioritized by how much value it is to the business.
Purpose	To determine what specific “stuff” the team should focus on.
Ordering	It is prioritized by how valuable it is for the business.
Product Backlog  Grooming	Lower value functions are moved to the bottom of the list or removed entirely.
Large Items	Large items are called Epics.
PBIs	An entry within the Product Backlog, called “Product Backlog Item”.


Sprint Backlog
Definition	The Sprint Backlog are an ordered list of requirements.
Purpose	To show at which stage the work being worked on is in.
Source of items	The items are pulled from the Product Backlog by the development team.
How are items chosen?	They are picked based on priority and only picked based on what the team believes they can accomplish.
What does value
orientation vs. results orientation mean?	It means to focus on the value added to the customer, not JUST the product.
Task Board	The task board is where the spring backlog are listed and broken down into tasks.
Sprint Backlog Item	These items are broken down into tasks with each task having a planned maximum duration of two days.


 Burndown Chart
Purpose	The chart provides a daily measure of work remaining in an iteration.
How is it updated?	It is updated every day with how much the team has completed that day.
How often is
it used?	The chart will be updated every day and assessed daily.
Significance?	The significance of the chart is critical to the project, as it is used to estimate whether the team can do a certain amount of work in the given amount of time or not.
User Stories

Definition	User stories are used as a basis got defining the requirements of the project, determining what will be focused on.
Purpose	This is the primary way for the client to influence the project.
Format	Small note cards.
Source	The source is the client.
Attributes for completeness	They need a name, brief narrative, an acceptance criteria, and the defined conditions.

Estimation

Story Points 	Story points are based on relative effort, with an agreed upon basis from the team.
Planning Poker	Planning poker is based on the Fibonacci Sequence, where they have numbers of 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, etc. Each member puts down a card with a written number of how many points they believe the task will take, if there is a difference in numbers between what the team members put, they will have to discuss why they put down such a time.
Fibonacci
Sequence	The sequence is a type of series where the two previous numbers are added together, 0, 1, 1, 2, 3, 5, 8, 13… etc.


